<item>
            <title>[LU-2250] Crash due to selinux on 1.8 client</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2250</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre 2.3.54 Client with selinux enabled does not exhibit this crash.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Setup:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;All CentOS 6.3 VMware images (x86_64)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Shared MDS/MGS on one VM - lustre-2.3.54-2.6.32_279.5.1.el6_lustre.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
Single OSS - lustre-2.3.54-2.6.32_279.5.1.el6_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Client that crashed - lustre-client-1.8.8.60-wc1_2.6.32_279.5.1.el6.x86_64_g5a16f88&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;br/&gt;
While test &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2241&quot; title=&quot;symlink bug in 2.3.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2241&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2241&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
1?) create symlink with path of exactly 60 char long&lt;br/&gt;
2) Mount created FS on 1.8 client&lt;br/&gt;
3) ls in mounted directory -&amp;gt; CRASH&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>CentOS 6.3 throughout, Lustre 2.3.54 Servers (OSS, MDS, MGS) (selinux disabled), 1.8.8 Client (selinux enabled)</environment>
